🚀 AI-Assisted Cloud Migration Playbook

On-Prem Kubernetes + RabbitMQ + PostgreSQL + Prometheus → AWS

⸻

🎯 Objective

Migrate a distributed on-prem system to AWS using structured DevOps practices, with AI assistance for analysis, design, and optimization.

⸻

🧠 Tools Used
	•	Claude (architecture analysis, validation)
	•	GitHub Copilot (code generation)
	•	Terraform (Infrastructure as Code)
	•	Kubernetes (EKS)
	•	AWS Services (EKS, RDS, MQ, CloudWatch)

⸻

📌 Phase 0 — Preparation

Tasks
	•	Collect:
	•	Kubernetes manifests
	•	RabbitMQ configuration
	•	PostgreSQL setup details
	•	Prometheus configuration
	•	Remove/mask sensitive data

⸻

🔍 Phase 1 — System Assessment

Actions
	•	Identify:
	•	Stateless vs stateful services
	•	Service dependencies
	•	External integrations

Key Focus
	•	RabbitMQ clustering and durability
	•	PostgreSQL storage and replication
	•	Prometheus persistence

Output
	•	Architecture diagram
	•	Dependency map
	•	Risk list

⸻

⚠️ Phase 2 — Risk Analysis

Evaluate
	•	Data loss scenarios
	•	Downtime risks
	•	Network dependencies
	•	Storage differences (on-prem vs cloud)

Key Risks
	•	RabbitMQ message loss
	•	PostgreSQL inconsistency
	•	Kubernetes storage mismatch
	•	Monitoring gaps during migration

Output
	•	Risk mitigation plan

⸻

🏗️ Phase 3 — Target AWS Architecture

Mapping

On-Prem Component	AWS Equivalent
Kubernetes	EKS
PostgreSQL	RDS (Multi-AZ)
RabbitMQ	Amazon MQ / EKS
Prometheus	EKS + CloudWatch


⸻

Design Principles
	•	High Availability (Multi-AZ)
	•	Private networking (VPC)
	•	IAM-based security
	•	Cost optimization

⸻

⚖️ Phase 4 — Decision Making

RabbitMQ
	•	Option 1: Amazon MQ
	•	Option 2: Self-managed on EKS

PostgreSQL
	•	Option 1: RDS
	•	Option 2: Self-managed

Evaluate
	•	Cost
	•	Operational overhead
	•	Failure recovery

⸻

🧪 Phase 5 — Failure Scenario Planning

Simulate
	•	Node failure (EKS)
	•	DB failover
	•	RabbitMQ crash
	•	Network partition

Define
	•	Recovery strategy
	•	Auto-healing mechanisms

⸻

⚙️ Phase 6 — Infrastructure as Code

Build using Terraform
	•	VPC (public/private subnets)
	•	EKS cluster
	•	RDS instance
	•	RabbitMQ setup
	•	IAM roles

Best Practices
	•	Modular design
	•	Remote state
	•	Environment separation

⸻

🔍 Phase 7 — Terraform Review

Validate
	•	Security groups
	•	IAM roles
	•	Cost optimization
	•	Missing resources

⸻

☸️ Phase 8 — Kubernetes Migration

Tasks
	•	Update manifests for EKS:
	•	Storage classes (EBS)
	•	Ingress (ALB)
	•	Autoscaling
	•	Validate:
	•	Health checks
	•	Resource limits

⸻

🐘 Phase 9 — PostgreSQL Migration

Strategy
	•	Replication (logical/streaming)
	•	Data validation
	•	Controlled cutover

Requirements
	•	Minimal downtime
	•	Rollback plan

⸻

🐰 Phase 10 — RabbitMQ Migration

Strategy
	•	Federation / Shovel plugin
	•	Dual-write during migration
	•	Queue synchronization

Goal
	•	Zero/low message loss

⸻

📊 Phase 11 — Monitoring & Observability

Setup
	•	Prometheus on EKS
	•	Grafana dashboards
	•	CloudWatch integration

Ensure
	•	Metrics continuity
	•	Alerting setup

⸻

🧪 Phase 12 — Sandbox Validation

Deploy in sandbox AWS account

Validate
	•	Application functionality
	•	Load handling
	•	Failover scenarios

⸻

🔁 Phase 13 — Optimization

Improve
	•	Cost efficiency
	•	Performance
	•	Security

Final Check
	•	Identify gaps
	•	Validate production readiness

⸻

🤖 AI-Assisted Workflow (How to Use)

During each phase:
	•	Use Claude to:
	•	Analyze configs
	•	Suggest improvements
